      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joan Bergeron Troche" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joan Bergeron Troche" href="/user/show/21947494-joan-bergeron-troche">Joan Bergeron Troche</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer660134163" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17559005529666020499">In reading this book, you cannot help but fall in love with the Yager family as they take in a stranger named Amber. It is obvious that Amber is very cautious and has a painful past. God uses the family to show Amber His love and open her heart towards Him.<br/><br/>If anything could be changed about this book, it is that I would encourage the author to slow the pace of the book down and give us more. The pace seemed too fast in both the way the setting was created in the first chapter and in how the fami</span>
  <span id="freeText17559005529666020499" style="display:none">In reading this book, you cannot help but fall in love with the Yager family as they take in a stranger named Amber. It is obvious that Amber is very cautious and has a painful past. God uses the family to show Amber His love and open her heart towards Him.<br /><br />If anything could be changed about this book, it is that I would encourage the author to slow the pace of the book down and give us more. The pace seemed too fast in both the way the setting was created in the first chapter and in how the family interacted with Amber and amongst themselves. It made me feel as though I was missing out on things. I would love more details about the times they spent together at work and at gatherings. I found myself thinking "Wow! That happened quickly!" at various points. The book was rather short at 157 pages and I would gladly have read through many more pages.<br /><br />I received this book for free in exchange for my honest review</span>
  <a data-text-id="17559005529666020499" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


